# InventorAI

An open-source AI assistant designed to help inventors, makers, and innovators turn ideas into reality.
This project is currently in the concept stage!

## Why this project exists

Many people have promising technical ideas but lack the resources, knowledge, or financial means to navigate the innovation process.

Patent research, market analysis, technical documentation, and manufacturer discovery can be overwhelming and expensive for individuals.

InventorAI aims to lower these barriers and make the early stages of invention more accessible.

## Vision

Create a free and open platform that helps users:

* Structure and document invention ideas
* Explore existing patents and prior art
* Analyze similar products and solutions
* Assess technical feasibility
* Identify potential manufacturers
* Generate draft technical descriptions
* Track and organize development progress

## Core Principles

* Open Source
* Transparency
* Privacy First
* Accessible to everyone
* Community Driven

## Who can contribute?

We welcome:

* Software developers
* AI engineers
* Patent researchers
* Product designers
* Inventors and makers
* Technical writers
* Curious people with ideas

No programming experience is required to participate.

## Current Status

This project is currently in the concept stage.

We are looking for contributors, feedback, criticism, and discussion to determine whether such a platform could become useful to the inventor community.

## Origin

The idea originated from the observation that many people struggle to move from an initial invention idea to practical implementation.

The project initiator is not a professional software developer and views this repository as an invitation to collaborate, discuss, and experiment together.

This document was created with the assistance of AI and serves as a starting point for community discussion.
